column5: WTG, Matt!  That's a good harbinger for this Wednesday!
PBs are always something to celebrate.  Nice-looking fish, congrats!  Mike

Was out fishing today and got two personal bests. One smallmouth that was 19 inches. The musky i caught was larger than my 40 inch measuring sticker. I am thinking maybe 43-44 inchs. Both fish were released.
SWEEEEET!!!! Congrats!!!   Looks like a very successful vacation for you!!
great catch!  congrats on the PB
Those are some nice new pb's WTG!!!
way to go!!  those are both nice looking fish.  jason
Congrats Dude, a couple of beauties there.
Great Stuff Matt...bet you don't get those in Kentucky  Maureen
Awesome day dude. Congrats!!
great job!!!!  cheeers!
Nice Ski, the bass isn't to bad either..  Congrats on the personal best.
Nice fish.  Congrats on the personal bests!
Buds your on fire, WTG...
Great catch!!!!!!!    and congrats on both of your PB"s....big smallie & big musky, what an awesome combination,great pics of both fish too....cheers
Real nice fishes!
congrats dude..both are verryy nice fish
Great fish Matt. Nice memories to take back south with you.
those are some great fish there. congrats
awesome  thanks for sharing  John
Congrats!  And in my opinion, if you're gonna get a couple of pb's, those are the species to do it in.  Nice fish
Nice going Matt.  Boating those two sure beats sitting in the library at U of L.
Outstanding, Beautiful fish Matt!

It was a great day on the water. Those were the only two fish that I caught. What a nice break from school! Its so nice being back home. Its only for two weeks, but atleast i get to spend Canada day with my family on the lake.
Congratulations Matt!  Two fine looking fish!  Whopper
Very impressive.  That smallie is a monster.  Way to go.  Joey
Right on. congrats on the P.Bull
